Professional summary:
I’m someone who loves building things that actually work, fast, reliable, and useful tools that make life easier for people on Solana. I’ve spent the last two year experimenting, breaking things, and rebuilding them until they run clean. Most of my work happens privately, not because I’m hiding it, but because I push a lot of in-progress systems tied to live trading and automation.

What drives me is curiosity and problem-solving. I’ve built everything from transaction debuggers and token distributors to arbitrage engines and flash loan bots. A few examples: ARGUS (a Solana transaction debugger that explains failed transactions like a human would), Bounty Beacon (Merkle-based token distributor for community payouts), and Sweeper-UI (a clean way to close token accounts and reclaim rent).

I’m part engineer, part explorer, constantly testing new APIs, writing async systems, and helping devs onboard faster into the Jupiter and Solana ecosystems. I like translating hard technical problems into things people can actually use.

What makes me stand out isn’t just code, it’s consistency. I show up every day, I build, I learn, and I improve. I laser focus on solving problems that matter. I’m here to push the Solana ecosystem forward, I see it as my home and would love to join a team that is like minded and shares the same goals/ambition. Also two add I'm trilingual I speak French, English and Amharic fluently and Spanish semi-fluent.

Professional summary:
I’m a full-stack engineer with 8+ years of experience building production-grade financial and blockchain systems, specializing in Rust, Solana programs, backend APIs, and data infrastructure. My work sits at the intersection of on-chain protocol design, high-throughput backend services, and execution-focused product tooling.
Currently at Keel.fi, I design and ship Rust (Anchor)–based Solana programs that manage borrowing, lending, collateral, and automated rebalancing across multiple DeFi protocols. I also architect the backend microservices and data pipelines (PostgreSQL, ClickHouse, Redis, GraphQL) that power real-time risk calculations, position tracking, and execution automation. One of my proudest contributions is building systems that reliably coordinate on-chain execution with off-chain strategy engines under real-world market conditions.
Previously, I led development of Astralane, a Solana indexing and infrastructure platform processing 500K+ daily transactions, where I built low-latency indexers, analytics pipelines, and execution services used for trading, arbitrage, and DeFi strategies. This gave me deep exposure to Solana internals, protocol behavior, and performance-critical data systems at scale.
What sets me apart is my ability to own complex systems end-to-end — from Rust-based smart contracts and backend microservices to trading terminals and user-facing dashboards — while keeping a strong focus on correctness, performance, and long-term maintainability. I’m most excited by early-stage teams building serious financial infrastructure, where engineering quality and execution discipline matter more than hype.
